"Indications in Critically Ill Patients"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"490798",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"noninvasive positive-pressure ventilation",
"children":[
"NPPV"
]
},
" is the use of positive-pressure ventilation without the need for an invasive airway. NPPV may be used as the ventilatory mode of first choice in these conditions:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bcbda6",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic obstructive pulmonary disease",
"children":[
"COPD"
]
},
" exacerbations (not stable COPD)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9ab374",
"children":[
"cardiogenic pulmonary edema"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"090747",
"children":[
"neuromuscular disease"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7d30f1",
"children":[
"prevention of recurrent respiratory failure in recently extubated high-risk patients"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"05172f",
"children":[
"obesity-hypoventilation syndrome"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f0ec23",
"children":[
"The most common contraindications to NPPV include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c88f9f",
"children":[
"respiratory arrest"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1b5b64",
"children":[
"medical instability"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"58d7f6",
"children":[
"inability to protect airway and/or excessive secretions or nausea and vomiting"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"644d07",
"children":[
"uncooperative or agitated patient"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"72b44d",
"children":[
"Improvements in blood gas values and clinical condition should occur within 2 hours of starting NPPV. If not, intubation should be considered to avoid undue delay and prevent respiratory arrest."
]
}
]
}
]
